Taliban Suicide Bombers Kill Eight, Injure 21 People in Kabul
KABULâ€”Taliban suicide bombers struck in Kabul on Wednesday, killing eight people and injuring 21, one day after Afghanistan's new government agreed to allow U.S. and allied troops to remain in the country after the end of this year.
Early Wednesday morning, one attacker on foot targeted a bus carrying Afghan Ministry of Defense staff in western Kabul, killing seven Afghan troops and one civilian, according to Afghanistan's ministry of interior.